text: Yvonne Tillmann (born 10 October 1967) is a German former taekwondo practitioner. She represented West Germany at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the lightweight event. At the 1990 European Taekwondo Championships she won for Germany the bronze medal in the -55 kg category. She was three times German champion. She was a member of TC Garmisch-Partenkirchen in Garmisch-Partenkirchen. == References == Category:1967 births Category:Living people Category:Olympians for Germany Category:Taekwondo practitioners
